column5: hey guys, just lookin for ice info on leigh's bay and the other bays around like haviland and goulais. is it safe for fishing or is it even frozen over?
They are catching whitefish in leighs bay. I wouldn't think Haviland is ready yet but I really don't know...it has been pretty cold and no snow so maybe.  wormdangler should know

thanks for the help! do you happen to know how thick the ice is out on leigh's bay right now? and i already asked wormdangler, he says he hasnt heard anything about it. he did tell me that he only managed to get one perch today! lol
There are huts out there..must be enough...just stick to other people trails,
shhhhhhhhhh it was embarrasing!!! dont need to go tell the world! haha! ohhh and theres 8-9inches of ice on rock lake

I started fishing leighs bay almost 3 weeks ago. I was there last on the 23rd or 24th and there was 6 inches of good ice Fishing wasnt awesome but we caught fish every time Im sure there is a bunch of people there everyday now  Oh and haviland has shacks but......be careful   I'll be chasing trout in lake superiour park this weekend...  TDunn
Luck man, thats the best type of icefishing there is, miss it a ton. Put em back up there and tell no one where you went!
Yup Cant wait, hittin it this weekend as well...gonna be a great weekend for them

good luck.  i'll be back up in the park this weekend partaking in the years first 5 km hike.  i'm kind of scared actually.  the 2.5 km hike last weekend just about kicked my arse.  should be able to get some nice big brookie photos though ...

Good luck on the weekend boys...I'm gonna be up the Ranger Lake way, have 5 lakes we are gonna hit this weekend.. including one that we believe no one has fished in a few years for some brookies, I will let ya know how we make out!
try not to get so far into the wobblies that you never make it out!  LOL! good luck len!  we expect pictures!
I'll think of you guys on the snowshoes, while we're driving down the ice road on lotw....   Luc keep an eye out for those tubes for me!
nope nope sorry fished it! no more left for you ssmfishingguy
You're *supposed* to tell them there was a 10lb 'eye hanging off that Perch! crap...what kind of fisherman are you Gavin?!?
Haha, not gonna be a big drinking weekend.. too many spots to go, gonna be a soberish weekend, heavy on the fishing!!
You got a camp on Ranger SSMFishguy? Our family has one on the last subdivision before top park...

My really good friend has a camp up there pretty much right at KM 54, you turn down the road with the pink panther or you can go in from Collins Road.  Technically you can call it the 2nd subdivision of the 3 that are there.
Awesome, whos that? We're the Archibalds by the way

I go to the Farrell's camp, my buddy Nate is related to them (its his aunts camp) but we use it all the time all year long.  Archibald's sounds familiar sure I have seen the sign on the subdivision road.
You're right beside us hahah   . Are you Buczel?
Which Farrell are you thinking?? i think you are in the other subdivision.. cause the two people beside him are not Archibald's.  Are you guys down by where the pig roast happens every August.
There must be two Farrels on the lake   . We are definitely the next road over
isnt that a buczel holding that big pike with tdunn in the other topic??
Dont know, I dont know junior only the old timer
Haha no thats not Pat...Its me in the pic ..I kinda look like him with a beard tho I guess.....   TDunn
